agreement entered into in the first quarter of 2020. During the twelve months ended December 31, 2019, new
borrowings net of repayments were $13.2 billion, primarily due to the issuance of $10.5 billion of fixed rate senior notes
in 2019. For further discussion see Liquidity Matters in Note 1 to our Consolidated Financial Statements.
